  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.12.6\n\n### What happened?\n\nWhen running a fairly long script (about 3.5 minutes) using `--network localhost` with a node running in terminal started with `npx hardhat node`, the script fails with the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nHeadersTimeoutError: Headers Timeout Error\r\n    at Timeout.onParserTimeout [as _onTimeout] (/Users/joshkramer/Documents/VSCodeProjects/BKopy/bkopy-nft-contracts/node_modules/undici/lib/client.js:905:28)\r\n    at listOnTimeout (node:internal/timers:570:11)\r\n    at processTimers (node:internal/timers:511:7) {\r\n  code: 'UND_ERR_HEADERS_TIMEOUT'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe same script complete normally however, when running on the internal hardhat node when run without the '--network`\r\nspecifier, or when run on the polygon mumbai test net.    \r\n\r\nIn an effort to fix it, I added the following to my hardhat.config:  \"networks\" key:\r\n```\r\nlocal: {\r\n      url: \"http://localhost:8545\",\r\n      timeout: 100_000_000\r\n    },\r\n```\r\nbut no help.\r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\nhh run scripts/[scriptname].ts\r\n\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
